div.p:
How Dead? yes already; in the Aorist;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 , which we render not, ye shall dye, but ye have died, or now are dead. Man borne of a Woman is not borne (as you may think) into Life, but into Death. Ye that are most awake sit asleep with your Eyes open; and when ye walk about, ye walk like Ghosts. What? shall I tell my Hearers they are Dead? who then shall heare me? I know to whom I speake, to the Dead, that come hither to learne the way of Life. Thrice Noble and thrice worshipfull, thrice worthy and thrice welcome, that ye may truly know how dead ye are, I say, ye are thrice Dead; yes, three wayes,
Dead in Law, Dead by the Course of Nature, Dead by the▪ Covenant of Grace.
